to the editor what is so wrong with keeping notebooks especially when you are a united states senator who wants to provide excellent constituent service keep track of issues and make sure you have the correct information when you open your mouth news article june 4 many people in many other occupations do the same thing i have dated notebooks covering 10 to 12 years of a continuing project that i store in my basement every once in a while i go down and do a when did that happen search to find the context of an event or a reaction it is not weird or even highly unusual and it is certainly not compulsive noelle douglas minneapolis june 4 2003

